  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Investigating and designing solutions to maternal, newborn and child health challenges in Oyam District, Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women and babies in northern Uganda suffer very poor health and many die during pregnancy and childbirth. Oyam district is still recovering from 20 years of conflict that ruined health services. Although increasing numbers of women are now using the health services that are being rebuilt, many more are left behind. This project reaches out into villages using the successful approach of mobilising women&apos;s groups. It consults with women, men, local leaders, the Ministry of Health and health workers. By getting a fuller appreciation of the situation on the ground, it aims to make better recommendations for how best to help improve residents&#x2019; health.</narrative>
  </description>
